snippet.textDisplay: I’m impressed he managed to stay on his feet. LOL, by the time the dog got to his arm they lost half their momentum having to jump so high. If you’ve never been on the inside of a bite suit you do not know what it is like.  Watched some friends finish working dogs once and as everyone was wrapping up for the day someone let the old girl out of the house.  Since the guy was still in the bite suit they decided to see if the old girl still wanted to work.  It took her about two strides and she was back in her glory. Knocked him off of his feet and had an absolute blast.  Those types of dogs are a whole different ball game, and it is bred into them. The training the dogs and the handler’s go through is very impressive. Only very responsible people are given the privilege to work with such amazing animals. God bless our police and military.
